Japanese Bought Net 409.9 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-10-19T23:54:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/japanese-bought-net-409-9-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Oct. 14 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 409.9 billion yen ($5.3 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 20.9 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 12.1 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 418.7 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 94.8 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 86.2 billion yen in stocks, and sold 1340.6 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 1349.2
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  